number.description: Line number in the file to comment on. Defaults to null.

path.description: Relative path of the file to comment on.

position.description: Line index in the diff to comment on.

sha.description: SHA of the commit to comment on.

total.description: The Total number of commits authored by the contributor.

force.description: Boolean indicating whether to force the update or to make sure the update is a fast-forward update. The default is false, so leaving this out or setting it to false will make sure you’re not overwriting work.

sha.description: String of the SHA1 value to set this reference to.

items.description: An Array of IP addresses in CIDR format specifying the Git servers at GitHub.
An Array of IP addresses in CIDR format specifying the addresses that incoming service hooks will originate from.

billing_email.description: Billing email address. This address is not publicized.

auto_init.description: True to create an initial commit with empty README. Default is false.

gitignore_template.description: Desired language or platform .gitignore template to apply. Use the name of the template without the extension. For example, "Haskell" Ignored if auto_init parameter is not provided.

has_downloads.description: True to enable downloads for this repository, false to disable them. Default is true.

has_issues.description: True to enable issues for this repository, false to disable them. Default is true.

has_wiki.description: True to enable the wiki for this repository, false to disable it. Default is true.

private.description: True to create a private repository, false to create a public one. Creating private repositories requires a paid GitHub account.

team_id.description: The id of the team that will be granted access to this repository. This is only valid when creating a repo in an organization.

parent.description: Is present when the repo is a fork. Parent is the repo this repo was forked from.

source.description: Is present when the repo is a fork. Source is the ultimate source for the network.

object.description: String of the SHA of the git object this is tagging.

date.description: Timestamp of when this object was tagged.

email.description: String of the email of the author of the tag.

name.description: String of the name of the author of the tag.

type.description: String of the type of the object we’re tagging. Normally this is a commit but it can also be a tree or a blob.

sha.description: SHA1 checksum ID of the object in the tree.

mode.description: One of 100644 for file (blob), 100755 for executable (blob), 040000 for subdirectory (tree), 160000 for submodule (commit) or 120000 for a blob that specifies the path of a symlink.

sha.description: SHA1 checksum ID of the object in the tree.

email.description: Note: The returned email is the user’s publicly visible email address (or null if the user has not specified a public email address in their profile).
